/boot - boot loader (GRUB configuration)
/root  - root use home directory
/dev - System Devices (disk,cdrom, speakers)
/etc - Configuration files
/usr/bin - Everyday user commands- For all users
/usr/sbin - Filesystem Commands - Only for root/System Daemons User
/opt - optional addon applications
/proc - Running Process (Only exist in Memory)
/lib - C programming libraries files
/tmp - Directory for temporary files - 7 days retention policy 
/home - Directory for user
/var - System logs
/run - System Daemon starts up - .lock files sit here
/mnt - to mount external file system
/media - for CD ROMs mounts
